<ContentLayout title="Wilds Endgame">
  <Section>
    <Comment> last updated for Gogmazios and AT Jin Dahaad </Comment>

    <p>
      These are the current endgame builds for Title Update 4.5, which added Arch Tempered Arkveld. All of these builds assume you've completed the main story and have access to the
      highest rarity Gogma Artian weapons, plus pretty much all decorations and armor pieces.
    </p>

    <ExternalLinkButton href="/wilds/builds/endgame-tu2" name="Old Tu2 Builds" />
  </Section>

  <Section title="Weapons">
    <p>
      Artian Weapons just got even better with the new Gogmazios reinforcement system, allowing you
      to get armor-exclusive skills and even more stat bonuses. For a full guide on how the system
      works exactly, or how to perform save scumming, check out the guide by Masuku.
    </p>

    <NavigationButton
      href="https://lescarnetsdelawycademie.fr/gogmazios-weapons/"
      text="in-depth gogma artian guide"
      emoji="📓"
    />

    <p>
      When crafting new Artian weapons, make sure to pick 3 parts of the same element, all with <b
        >attack infusion</b
      >. This maximizes your chances of getting the desired element with optimal production bonuses.
      Avoid affinity infusion, it is noticeably worse.
    </p>

    <p>
      When you upgrade your Artian weapon, you can choose between attack, affinity, or element
      focus. Depending on the focus, you receive different bonus stats. Both element and attack
      focus are strong options, though element is technically the slightly superior choice (roughly
      0.05% more damage).
    </p>

    <p>
      Depending on your focus, the optimal stat rolls differ slightly. Regardless of build, always
      aim for 1x Sharpness EX and 2x Attack EX. If you went with element focus, look for 2x Attack
      III. With attack focus, we want to balance out the negative affinity, so choose 1x Affinity EX
      and 1x Attack III.
    </p>

    <p>
      There are very few matchups where maxing out element instead of attack is strictly better.
      Gogmazios himself, for example, is one case due to his Phase 3 weakness to Dragon. So if you
      don't want to craft like 11 different weapons, just max out raw.
    </p>

    <ImageCard
      src={gogma_artian}
      alt="reinforcement bonuses"
      caption="A dragon gogma artian lance with full attack infusion, element focus, 1x sharpness EX, 2x attack EX, 1x attack III and 1x attack II. Almost a max roll"
      maxWidth="500px"
    />

    <p>
      For the skills, aim for <b>Gore Magala's Tyranny</b> (Gore) or <b>Leviathan's Fury</b> (Lagiacrus)
      as the series skill. Then aim for <b>Lord's Soul</b> (Guts) as the group skill. These are by far
      the best-in-slot options.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Element vs Raw">
    <p>
      Since Gogma Artian weapons can all reach the same raw damage, using elemental ones simply adds
      free damage on top. If possible, craft 6 different lances (one for each element plus one
      status/raw weapon) to maximize your damage potential across all matchups.. Using the right
      element typically adds 5-15% damage, which really adds up over time.
    </p>

    <p>Check the matchup table to see which element works best against each monster.</p>

    <NavigationButton href="/wilds/data/match-ups" text="matchup chart" emoji="📊" />

    <p>
      If you want to stick with raw weapons, blast is generally the best option, though paralysis is
      also solid for the openings it creates.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <Section title="RNG Charms">
    <p>
      The August update added a new RNG charm system. These charms allow you to potentially get more
      weapon skills. Aim for a level 1 weapon slot combined
      with skills like
      <b>Critical Eye 3</b>, <b>Offensive Guard 3</b>, <b>Master's Touch 1</b>, or <b>Razor Sharp 3</b> on the charm.
    </p>

    <StyledList
      items={[
        {
          text: 'Weapon 1 Slot',
          subtext: 'to fit a level of crit boost or element attack',
          emoji: '🛡️',
        },
        {
          text: 'Weapon Skills',
          subtext: "All 3 levels of Critical Eye, Offensive Guard, Razor Sharp or  1 level of Master's Touch",
          emoji: '🗡️',
        },
      ]}
    />

    <p>
      This usually allows you to slot in more Crit Boost or get extra affinity from Critical Eye.
    </p>
  </Section>

  <InfoBox>
    All sets relying on Gore/Lord's Soul being on the weapon have an alternative build that can be
    made by replacing Gore with Lagiacrus Legs and adding 1-2 levels of Latent Power. These sets are very
    minimally (1-2%) weaker than the Gore versions. You can hopefully figure out the details
    yourself 🙏
  </InfoBox>

  <Section title="Gorcher" emoji="🦠">
    <p>
      This is theoretically the highest damage set available. It utilizes <b>Lord's Soul</b> and <b
        >Bloodlust</b
      >
      to reach massive raw and affinity numbers. It maxes out every core skill Lance wants, and as a
      bonus, also unlocking Binding Counter and Scorcher.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Transcended Guardian Rathalos pieces are incredibly efficient, letting us max out the core
      skills and squeeze in a level of <b>Scorcher</b>, which got significant buffs in title update
      4. It now deals fixed damage and has lower cooldown for procs, making it a powerful damage
      skill (even against fire resistant monsters).
    </p>

    <p>
      <b>Binding Counter</b> gives +25 raw for 90 seconds after a power clash or when recovering from
      grabs or web effects. Since a lot of the endgame fights can be powerclashed, or have some other
      way to trigger it, it's a great skill to have.
    </p>

