        in theory, and even more in practice.
      </p>
    </InfoBox>
  </Section>

  <Section title="Scorcher" emoji="🔥">
    <p>
      You can also fully lean into <b>Scorcher</b> and reach level 2 by running 3 pieces of G. Rathalos
      and 1 point on your weapon. Since Scorcher deals fixed damage, it's great against monsters with
      bad raw hitzones (like Gore). It also scales with fire damage and the monster's fire weakness,
      making it able to outdamage Gorcher in certain matchups.
    </p>

    <p>
      The tradeoff is lower overall affinity, which means faster sharpness loss. The math gets
      complicated quickly, there are a lot of variables at play: monster hitzone values, hit uptime,
      internal skill cooldowns, and more. That said, Gorcher tends to be the more consistent choice
      across most matchups, whereas Full Scorcher shines against monsters with low raw hitzone
      values or when you're not having high hit uptime.
    </p>

    <p>
      This set also uses 2 AT Jin Dahaad pieces, unlocking <b>Binding Counter</b> for a solid raw boost
      whenever it can be triggered.
    </p>

