  <Section title="Anti Gogmazios" emoji="🔱">
    <p>
      Gogmazios has an extreme dragon weakness in phase 3, making it one of the few matchups where
      going full element is clearly worth it. Running 4 Gogmazios pieces unlocks <b
        >Mutual Hostility</b
      > level 2, which gives a massive element boost while the monster is enraged. You also get a temporary
      shield, making some of his scarier one-shot attacks much more manageable.
    </p>

    <p>
      Since Gogmazios weapons require materials that only drop from this fight, crafting a dedicated
      dragon weapon makes sense once you're farming him regularly. For the build to work you only
      need Gore on the weapon, which is more forgiving to roll than a fully optimized Gorcher setup.
      With element reinforcements (2x Element EX, 2x Element II), you're looking at around 20% more
      damage in phase 3 compared to Gorcher.
    </p>

    <p>
      The fight plays quite differently across its three phases. In phases 1 and 2 he's weaker to
      fire and since in the non-liquid state the hitzones are very low you can even run Mind's Eye.
      Phase 3 is where this build really shines, Offensive Guard is very hard to activate so run
      Crit Element on your dragon set instead, and slot Guard Up if you want extra comfort against
      his fire bubble attacks, otherwise drop it and run Crit Boost 3 instead.
    </p>

